<TITLE> Shab-e-Miraj to fall on July 30 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 5 (bdnews24.com)  The month of Rajab, 1429 (AH), begins Saturday, with the holy night of Shab-e-Miraj falling on July 30, a government statement said following an announcement by the National Moon Sighting Committee on Friday. The moon of the Rajab month was seen in the sky of Bangladesh Friday, the meeting of the committee said. Religious secretary Muhammad Ataur Rahman, also the vice president of the committee, presided over the meeting. bdnews
